title: ARY News Headlines |PTI government to complete tenure| 6PM | 5 Oct 2019
text:
PM advises AJK people against crossing LoC into occupied Kashmir.

President urges world to recognize India’s state terrorism in occupied Kashmir.

PTI government to complete tenure, says Firdous Ashiq Awan.

Sindh govt extends Rangers’ special powers for three months.

FM Qureshi asks JUI-F chief to avoid march towards Islamabad.

Number plates with ‘Ajrak’ logos to be introduced in Sindh.

#HappyBirthdayKhanSahb trends on Twitter as PM turns 67.

Fazl vows to go ahead with Azadi March at all costs.

Pak-Iran travel gate at Taftan to remain closed for 16 days.
